                  </hi>. I have lived at No. 1, Perseverance Court, close to the railway arch for two years—I have never experienced any incon<lb></lb>venience or annoyance from Mr. Burgess's—if there had been any smell I think it would have come through the arch—I have gone through the arch and have not smelt anything offensive—I am out at all times, and have my windows and doors open; I never had occasion to close them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
